CommonFields.Title: Core@Double-Shell Structured Nanocomposites: A Route to High Dielectric Constant and Low Loss Material
Author: Huang, Yanhui
Huang, Xingyi
Schadler, Linda S.
He, Jinliang
Jiang, Pingkai
CommonFields.Location: Department of Polymer Science and Engineering, Shanghai Key Laboratory of Electrical Insulation and Thermal Aging, Shanghai Jiao Tong University, Shanghai 200240, China

Mixing.Description: The sodium acrylate monomer was synthesized by slowly adding a concentrated NaOH aqueous solution to an excess 30 vol % acrylate acid acetone solution under an ice bath with continuous stirring.

ChemicalUsed.description: excess 30 vol% acrylate acid acetone solution

ChooseParameter.Other: The product precipitated as a white powder and was later recovered by filtering, acetone washing and subsequent vacuum drying.

Mixing.Description: The synthesized sodium acrylate (6.0 g) was dissolved in 10 mL of DI water with insoluble impurities filtered out.
Initiator-grafted BT NPs (0.5 g) were added to the solution, followed by 30 min sonication.

Additive.Description: One mmole of CuBr (0.1430 g) and 0.2 mmol of CuBr2 (0.0450 g) were added.
One mmole of CuBr (0.1430 g) and 0.2 mmol of CuBr2 (0.0450 g) were added.

Mixing.Description: bpy (2.5 mmol, 0.390 g) was later added into 2 mL of ethanol solution via syringe.
stirred at room temperature for certain amount of time

ChooseParameter.Other: The polymerization time was controlled and the reaction was immediately quenched by pouring the solution into a 20 mL aqueous solution containing 1 mmol of CuBr2 (0.224 g) and 2 mmol of bpy (0.312 g).
The NPs were recovered after three cycles of DMF wash and centrifuging at 9000 rpm for 10 min.

Additive.Description: pH value was adjusted to 9 by adding 0.1M NaOH.

Precision Premier II ferroelectric polarization tester

Thermogravimetric_Analysis.Description: with a heating rate of 20 C/min under a nitrogen flow
